==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Platinichloric
<hw>Plat`i*ni*chlo"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, an acid
consisting of platinic chloride and hydrochloric acid, and obtained as a
brownish red crystalline substance, called <xex>platinichloric</xex>, or
<xex>chloroplatinic</xex>, <xex>acid</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Platiniferous</ent>⟦br⟧
